n**\n\nThe `fileExists` helper at line 518 is the **fourth** copy of this exact function in the codebase:\n- `/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/utils.go:36`\n- `/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint/temporary.go:829`\n- `/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/common.go:990`\n- `/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/integration_test/manual_commit_untracked_files_test.go:518`\n\nThe integration test cannot import from the `cli` or `strategy` packages without creating a dependency cycle, so a local copy is defensible. However, it could be defined in one of the existing integration test helper files (e.g., `testenv.go` or `hooks.go`) to be shared across test files within the same `integration` package.\n\n**Recommendation:** Move `fileExists` to `/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/integration_test/testenv.go` so other test files in the package can reuse it. (Check whether it already exists in that file first.)\n\n**4c. Confused test logic in `TestShadow_UntrackedFilesAcrossMultipleSessions`**\n\nLines 323-329 of the test file contain an in-code debate:\n\n```go\n// session2-config.yaml was created after the first checkpoint, so it should be deleted\n// Actually, it was created before the checkpoint, so it should be preserved\n// Let me reconsider the test logic...\nif fileExists(filepath.Join(env.RepoDir, \"session2-config.yaml\")) {\n    t.Log(\"session2-config.yaml still exists (created before checkpoint)\")\n}\n```\n\nThis is an anti-pattern: a comment expressing uncertainty about the test's own expectations, followed by a non-asserting check (`t.Log` instead of `t.Error`). The test passes regardless of the file's existence, which means it is not actually testing anything meaningful about `session2-config.yaml`.\n\n**Analysis of the correct behavior:** `session2-config.yaml` is created *before* the `SimulateUserPromptSubmit` call for session 2, so it gets captured in `UntrackedFiles